	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>agility and dexterity for ogres and trolls</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Feb 11th 5:34 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=171969><span id= >Lady guineapig</span></a><br><span id=notbold>202 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.80]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>&nbsp;&nbsp; Ok, armor class and hit points being our primary focus has been made clear to me. However the arguement over the importance of strength still hasn't found a conclusion in my mind. I have read many places that the bonus for extra strength is minimal compared to how long you can survive a fight by using a agility to avoid taking damage. <br><br>   I would really appreciate a higher lvl warrior's opinion on this. I have a lvl 45 Enchantress ans don't mind spending my money on gear for my new warrior. I can't decide on Ogre or Troll? I like the look of female trolls more than female ogres but the str/sta vs. agi/dex question comes into play there as well. So does the regen ability of trolls vs. their exp penalty. Is the regen worth it? And is the exp. penalty THAT HIGH?<br><br>  Anyway, I'm mainly curious about puting my base stat points into agi/dex since both races have a high str to begin with. But which stat is the hardest to obtain cheaply through gear? Is it str, or dex/agi?<br><br>I realise I just asked way too any questions but tanking is completely foreign to me and I've heard too many opinions on the matter and would like some facts from people who've been there. Thanks in advance for any help!!! :)</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
