	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=126408><span id=Sage>Bikamar</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>302 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>STR is by far the easiest stat to upgrade.&nbsp;&nbsp;DEX/AGI are slighty easier to improve than STA.<br><br>I think that your focus on STR to shorten a fight through increased damage, and AGI to reduce the damage you take while fighting is probably too much.<br><br>As a warrior, the damage you do and the damage you take is primarily affected by the gear you wear (weapons damge/delay and AC).  Overall, STR and AGI have very little effect on combat (exception: AGI under 75 can have a noticable effect on your damage avoidance).<br><br>If I were to go back and reroll my warrior, I would duimp my points between STA (most) and DEX.<br>(why? STA = more HPs, DEX = more chance of procs and faster improvements with weapon skills).<br><br>As for regen, as Meirril said, when your fighting mobs that hit for hundreds of points very quickly it will make little to no difference.  If you think the trolls look better, go with the troll :)<br><br>Meirril: STR only adds to the &quot;Damage&quot; part of the ATK value, not the &quot;To Hit&quot; part.  It does not contribute to the damage bonus on weapons in any way.</p>&nbsp;<br>"...come back here ya coward! I'll bite yer kneecaps off..."<br><br>It's not the class that makes the player - it's the player that makes the class</td></td></tr>
